article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- — Honor Huff's 31 points led Chattanooga over East Tennessee State 84-71 on Wednesday night. Huff was 10 of 17 shooting (9 for 16 from 3-point range) for the Mocs (18-8, 10-3 Southern Conference). Trey Bonham scored 14 points and added eight assists. Tyler Millin finished with 12 points. The Buccaneers (13-13, 5-8) were led in scoring by Quimari Peterson, who finished with 22 points and three steals. Jaden Seymour added 19 points, six rebounds and two steals for East Tennessee State. Maki Johnson had 11 points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
